  "text": "The model was validated by comparison to published data; to xenon uptake data in humans from a different model [CITATION_1] and from experimental measurements of xenon blood concentrations during wash-in to pigs [CITATION_2] . Both comparisons (Figs. 2 and 3) show that the current model can accurately determine the rate of disposition of the gas in the body. We note that this accuracy is achieved in spite of the fact that the model does not account for mixing or circulation in the arterial blood compartment.",
